comments.message: What is this?
https://issues.sierrawireless.com/browse/MANGOH-1
Jen: We have just started using JIRA for mangOH.  I have created the first issue to track these changes to the GPIO Expander code.  Tom's link is to the issue.
Why expander1InterruptPinSpec uses EXPANDER_2_INDEX, And expander3 uses EXPANDER_2_INDEX as well?
This is because the interrupt pin from expander1 goes to a GPIO on expander 2.  Likewise, the interrupt pin from expander 3 goes to a GPIO on expander 2.
I feel your pain.
haha!  I hope you reviewed every one of those 9000 lines of code :-p
Should be 'Deactivate'
Done
Why it's binded to le_gpioPin2?
gpioService.le_gpioPin2 is the GPIO on the WP85 that is connected to the interrupt line that runs from expander 2 to the WP85.

commits.commitMessage:
Substantially change gpioExpander API

- Remove request and release functions because there is potential for a
  race if one thread does a request for a pin on a GPIO expander and
  then another thread makes a request for a different pin on the same
  GPIO expander before the first thread has called Release().
- Change the interface so that clients don't need to care about which
  expander a GPIO is on.
- Simplify I2C switch initialization.
- Rewrite GpioExpanderDemo to turn on/off LED_CARD_DETECT_IOTx as IoT
  cards are inserted/removed.

Change-Id: I435d6848825fe9fea77d17045b3e2aea2179b7ac
commits.subject: Substantially change gpioExpander API
